'''Calvin Hartwell''' (December 17, 1849 – May 19, 1920) was a [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]] politician who served as a member of the [[Pasadena City Council|Pasadena Board of Trustees]]  from 1895-1898, [[List of mayors of Pasadena, California|Mayor of Pasadena, California]] from 1896-1898, [[Los Angeles County Assessor]] from 1906–1910, and [[Los Angeles County Coroner]] from 1908-1920. He was born near Sandusky, Ohio.

